page.title: 19TANNOCH LOCH
page.content: {Tannoch Loch }is a well known Milgavie beauty spot and a good place to find ducks and other wild life.The birds are very tame and when you go there they want to be fed.There are Coots and Mallards and little ducklings which are sometimes eaten by Herons. The trees round about Tannoch reflect into the water and make it look colourful.The wild flowers on the banks are attractive.The nests are usually in the reeds and rushes and very well camouflaged. The loch is private and the people from round about it can go for a row in it, if they have a boat. Tannoch Loch is a peaceful place to visit.
